<title>REPEATEDLY-DO-BEHAVIOURS</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Language" content="en-gb">
</head>
<body>
	<h3><i>I repeatedly add behaviours.</i></h3>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	<p><b>REPEATEDLY-DO-BEHAVIOURS</b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>substitute-text-area-for cycle-duration 1                         
substitute-text-area-for comment Notes                                               
do-every cycle-duration
  [add-behaviours list-of-micro-behaviours "Behaviours" []]
;comment</pre>
	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Variants</h2>

	<p>Just add micro-behaviours to the list by clicking on a micro-behaviour 
	and navigating back to this page. Change the number in the box to change the 
	delay between cycles. Note that the micro-behaviours added should not 
	themselves use <b>
	<a target="_blank" href="http://resources.modelling4all.org/documents/programming-guide#toc0">
	do-every</a></b> or the like but should run once.</p>

	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>
	<p><a href="ADD-BEHAVIOURS.html">ADD-BEHAVIOURS</a> -- Adds behaviours once.</p>

	<p><a href="DO-AFTER.html">DO-AFTER</a> -- Delays the 
	addition of a list of micro-behaviours.</p>
<p><a href="WHEN.html">WHEN</a> -- Adds and removes micro-behaviours the first 
time that conditions are true.</p>
<p><a href="WHENEVER.html">WHENEVER</a> -- Adds and removes micro-behaviours 
every time conditions are true.</p>
	

	<p>

	<a href="ADD-BEHAVIOURS-TO-LINKS.html">ADD-BEHAVIOURS-TO-LINKS</a> -- Adds 
	micro-behaviours to links (rather than agents).</p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>
	<p>This uses the Modelling4All NetLogo command <b>
	<a target="_blank" href="http://resources.modelling4all.org/documents/programming-guide#toc0">
	do-every</a></b> to schedule the addition of the micro-behaviours. The 
	micro-behaviours typically only run once and remove themselves.</p>
	<h2>History</h2>
	<p>This was first implemented by Ken Kahn on 6 October 2009. 

